db:abstract.db:para: The QJsonObject class encapsulates a JSON object.
This class was introduced in Qt 5.0.

db:note.db:para: All functions in this class are reentrant.

db:listitem.db:para: QJsonObject is part of JSON Support in QtImplicitly Shared Classes

db:section.db:title: Detailed Description
db:section.db:para: A JSON object is a list of key value pairs, where the keys are unique strings and the values are represented by a QJsonValue.

A QJsonObject can be converted to and from a QVariantMap. You can query the number of (key, value) pairs with size(), insert(), and remove() entries from it and iterate over its content using the standard C++ iterator pattern.
QJsonObject is an implicitly shared class, and shares the data with the document it has been created from as long as it is not being modified.
You can convert the object to and from text based JSON through QJsonDocument.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::ConstIterator
db:section.db:para: Qt-style synonym for QJsonObject::const_iterator.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::Iterator
db:section.db:para: Qt-style synonym for QJsonObject::iterator.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::key_type
db:section.db:para: Typedef for QString. Provided for STL compatibility.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::mapped_type
db:section.db:para: Typedef for QJsonValue. Provided for STL compatibility.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::size_type
db:section.db:para: Typedef for int. Provided for STL compatibility.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::QJsonObject()
db:section.db:para: Constructs an empty JSON object.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.4] QJsonObject::QJsonObject(std::initializer_list<QPair<QString, QJsonValue>> args)
db:section.db:para: Constructs a QJsonObject instance initialized from args initialization list. For example:
This function was introduced in Qt 5.4.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::QJsonObject(const QJsonObject &other)
db:section.db:para: Creates a copy of other.
Since QJsonObject is implicitly shared, the copy is shallow as long as the object does not get modified.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.10] QJsonObject::QJsonObject(QJsonObject &&other)
db:section.db:para: Move-constructs a QJsonObject from other.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.10.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::~QJsonObject()
db:section.db:para: Destroys the object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::iterator QJsonObject::begin()
db:section.db:para: Returns an STL-style iterator pointing to the first item in the object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::begin() const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::constBegin() const
db:section.db:para: Returns a const STL-style iterator pointing to the first item in the object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::constEnd() const
db:section.db:para: Returns a const STL-style iterator pointing to the imaginary item after the last item in the object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::constFind(const QString &key) const
db:section.db:para: Returns a const iterator pointing to the item with key key in the map.
If the map contains no item with key key, the function returns constEnd().

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::constFind(QLatin1String key) const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.

db:section.db:title: bool QJsonObject::contains(const QString &key) const
db:section.db:para: Returns true if the object contains key key.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] bool QJsonObject::contains(QLatin1String key) const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.

db:section.db:title: int QJsonObject::count() const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
Same as size().

db:section.db:title: bool QJsonObject::empty() const
db:section.db:para: This function is provided for STL compatibility. It is equivalent to isEmpty(), returning true if the object is empty; otherwise returning false.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::iterator QJsonObject::end()
db:section.db:para: Returns an STL-style iterator pointing to the imaginary item after the last item in the object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::end() const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::iterator QJsonObject::erase(QJsonObject::iterator it)
db:section.db:para: Removes the (key, value) pair pointed to by the iterator it from the map, and returns an iterator to the next item in the map.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::iterator QJsonObject::find(const QString &key)
db:section.db:para: Returns an iterator pointing to the item with key key in the map.
If the map contains no item with key key, the function returns end().

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] QJsonObject::iterator QJsonObject::find(QLatin1String key)
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::find(const QString &key) const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] QJsonObject::const_iterator QJsonObject::find(QLatin1String key) const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.

db:section.db:title: [static, since 5.5] QJsonObject QJsonObject::fromVariantHash(const QVariantHash &hash)
db:section.db:para: Converts the variant hash hash to a QJsonObject.
The keys in hash will be used as the keys in the JSON object, and the QVariant values will be converted to JSON values.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.5.

db:section.db:title: [static] QJsonObject QJsonObject::fromVariantMap(const QVariantMap &map)
db:section.db:para: Converts the variant map map to a QJsonObject.
The keys in map will be used as the keys in the JSON object, and the QVariant values will be converted to JSON values.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject::iterator QJsonObject::insert(const QString &key, const QJsonValue &value)
db:section.db:para: Inserts a new item with the key key and a value of value.
If there is already an item with the key key, then that item's value is replaced with value.
Returns an iterator pointing to the inserted item.
If the value is QJsonValue::Undefined, it will cause the key to get removed from the object. The returned iterator will then point to end().

db:section.db:title: bool QJsonObject::isEmpty() const
db:section.db:para: Returns true if the object is empty. This is the same as size() == 0.

db:section.db:title: QStringList QJsonObject::keys() const
db:section.db:para: Returns a list of all keys in this object.
The list is sorted lexographically.

db:section.db:title: int QJsonObject::length() const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
Same as size().

db:section.db:title: void QJsonObject::remove(const QString &key)
db:section.db:para: Removes key from the object.

db:section.db:title: int QJsonObject::size() const
db:section.db:para: Returns the number of (key, value) pairs stored in the object.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.10] void QJsonObject::swap(QJsonObject &other)
db:section.db:para: Swaps the object other with this. This operation is very fast and never fails.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.10.

db:section.db:title: QJsonValue QJsonObject::take(const QString &key)
db:section.db:para: Removes key from the object.
Returns a QJsonValue containing the value referenced by key. If key was not contained in the object, the returned QJsonValue is QJsonValue::Undefined.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.5] QVariantHash QJsonObject::toVariantHash() const
db:section.db:para: Converts this object to a QVariantHash.
Returns the created hash.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.5.

db:section.db:title: QVariantMap QJsonObject::toVariantMap() const
db:section.db:para: Converts this object to a QVariantMap.
Returns the created map.

db:section.db:title: QJsonValue QJsonObject::value(const QString &key) const
db:section.db:para: Returns a QJsonValue representing the value for the key key.
The returned QJsonValue is QJsonValue::Undefined if the key does not exist.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] QJsonValue QJsonObject::value(QLatin1String key) const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.

db:section.db:title: bool QJsonObject::operator!=(const QJsonObject &other) const
db:section.db:para: Returns true if other is not equal to this object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonObject &QJsonObject::operator=(const QJsonObject &other)
db:section.db:para: Assigns other to this object.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.10] QJsonObject &QJsonObject::operator=(QJsonObject &&other)
db:section.db:para: Move-assigns other to this object.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.10.

db:section.db:title: bool QJsonObject::operator==(const QJsonObject &other) const
db:section.db:para: Returns true if other is equal to this object.

db:section.db:title: QJsonValue QJsonObject::operator[](const QString &key) const
db:section.db:para: Returns a QJsonValue representing the value for the key key.
This does the same as value().
The returned QJsonValue is QJsonValue::Undefined if the key does not exist.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] QJsonValue QJsonObject::operator[](QLatin1String key) const
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.

db:section.db:title: QJsonValueRef QJsonObject::operator[](const QString &key)
db:section.db:para: Returns a reference to the value for key.

The return value is of type QJsonValueRef, a helper class for QJsonArray and QJsonObject. When you get an object of type QJsonValueRef, you can use it as if it were a reference to a QJsonValue. If you assign to it, the assignment will apply to the element in the QJsonArray or QJsonObject from which you got the reference.

db:section.db:title: [since 5.7] QJsonValueRef QJsonObject::operator[](QLatin1String key)
db:section.db:para: This is an overloaded function.
This function was introduced in Qt 5.7.
